description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Twilight Community Staff Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 - £24,907 - £30,615 pa pro rata + HCAS £3,784 - £4,592 pa pro rata&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like to work for an organisation that is progressive, innovative and provides quality care for families in Bromley? To find out what its like to work for Bromley Healthcare please view our videos on YouTube, search for Bromley healthcare and you will get a flavour of Bromley healthcare.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bromley Healthcare are currently recruiting for a number of Band 5 Twilight Community Nurses. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The team are &lt;strong&gt;busy &amp; dynamic and have patient care at the heart of all they do. Our work is crucial to the community as we aim to prevent hospital care for our patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that as a Community Nurse you will not lose clinical skills such as Picc lines/IV’s as these are skills that are very much key to being an excellent Community Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Community Nurse you will deal with a variety of patients in their own homes, the role will involve but is not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsibility for contributing to the holistic assessment, planning, delivery and evaluation of patient care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementing, monitoring and maintaining our high standards of care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Re-assessing and re-evaluating programmes of care when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being an active member of the team sharing best practice whenever possible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a challenging but ultimately rewarding position where you will be supported both within your teams and by regular reflection &amp; professional training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be able to work a minimum of 2 shifts per week across a 7 day week 6.30-10.30pm (4 hours) working across the borough of Bromley.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also work additional bank shifts if you wish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that Community Nursing roles are designated essential car users therefore applicants should have a current driving licence and access to a vehicle to be considered for this position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information, please see attached JD and PS.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lorna Redpath - Twilight Manager - lorna.redpath1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
